  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Since upgrading to `v22.12.0`, the `/eth/v1/remotekeys` endpoint on the Validator REST API does not work anymore.\r\n\r\n## Config\r\n\r\n```yaml\r\n# Validators API\r\nvalidator-api-port: 5062\r\nvalidator-api-enabled: true\r\nvalidator-api-docs-enabled: true\r\nvalidator-api-interface: \"0.0.0.0\"\r\nvalidator-api-keystore-file: \"/validator/store/validator_store.p12\"\r\nvalidator-api-keystore-password-file: \"/validator/store/validator_store.txt\"\r\nvalidator-api-host-allowlist: [\"127.0.0.1\", ...]\r\n```\r\n## Command\r\n\r\n`$ curl -s --insecure -H \"Authorization: Bearer x-y-z\" -H \"Accept: application/json\" https://127.0.0.1:5062/eth/v1/remotekeys | jq`\r\n\r\nHave also tested different IPs and hostnames (all allowed in the `validator-api-host-allowlist`), same result (works with `22.11`, SNI error with `22.12`.\r\n* 127.0.0.1\r\n* localhost\r\n* hostname\r\n* hostname.xyz\r\n\r\n## 22.11.0-jdk17-amd64\r\n\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n  \"data\": [\r\n    {\r\n      \"pubkey\": \"0xABC\",\r\n      \"url\": \"http://172.31.0.90:9000\",\r\n      \"readonly\": true\r\n    },\r\n    {\r\n      \"pubkey\": \"0xDEF\",\r\n      \"url\": \"http://172.31.0.90:9000\",\r\n      \"readonly\": true\r\n    }\r\n  ]\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n## 22.12.0-jdk17-amd64\r\n\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n  \"cause0\": \"org.eclipse.jetty.http.BadMessageException: 400: Invalid SNI\",\r\n  \"message\": \"Invalid SNI\",\r\n  \"url\": \"/eth/v1/remotekeys\",\r\n  \"status\": \"400\"\r\n}\r\n```",
