    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "To capture the discord discussion around this, 22.12.0 includes an upgrade to Javalin and Jetty, the libraries Teku uses for its REST APIs.  The Jetty upgrade added validation that the hostname the client specified via SNI matches one of the valid names listed in the SSL certificate and rejects the request with this \"Invalid SNI\" error if it does not.\r\n\r\nWill need to see the details of the actual SSL cert being used in this case to be entirely sure that's the issue here, but it's certainly a likely cause.\r\n\r\nI've started a docs PR to add instructions to generate a certificate that includes use multiple domain names: https://github.com/ConsenSys/doc.teku/pull/414 though it will need some cleaning up from someone with actual writing skills.",
